  "prompt": "What is the omen behind itchy palms?",
  "response": "The superstition surrounding itchy palms is an old one and varies across different cultures. Generally, there are two common beliefs associated with this phenomenon:\n\n1. **Itchy Right Palm**: In many cultures, an itchy right palm is considered a sign of good luck, specifically related to money. It is believed that you will either receive money or come into wealth soon. In some European traditions, this is thought to mean that money will be coming to you, while in certain Asian cultures, it could mean that you will have to pay out money.\n\n2. **Itchy Left Palm**: Conversely, an itchy left palm often has different interpretations. In some Western cultures, it's believed that an itchy left palm means you will lose money or spend money soon. However, in other traditions, like in some parts of Asia, an itchy left palm might indicate that money is coming your way.\n\nThese beliefs are purely superstitious and have no scientific backing. They are part of folklore and vary widely from one region to another. It's interesting to note how the same physical sensation can be interpreted in such diverse ways depending on cultural context.",
